-- Boston College, Ferris State Advance to NCAA Ice Hockey Final
-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 2012-04-06T04:25:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-06/boston-college-ferris-state-advance-to-ncaa-ice-hockey-final.html
Top-seeded  Boston College  and No. 14
seed Ferris State University advanced to the final in college
ice hockey’s national men’s tournament.  Boston College defeated sixth-seeded  Minnesota  6-1 and
Ferris State upset third-seeded Union College 3-1 in the
National Collegiate Athletic Association tournament yesterday at
Tampa Bay Times Forum.  The championship game is tomorrow in Tampa Bay.  Paul Carey scored twice for Boston College, which also got
goals from Steven Whitney, Kevin Hayes, Chris Kreider and Brian
Dumoulin. Jake Hansen gave Minnesota its only score at the start
of the third period.  In the earlier game, Aaron Schmit had two goals and Kyle
Bonis contributed the third for Ferris State. Daniel Carr had a
goal for Union in the first period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
 msillup@bloomberg.net  